{# Welcome-page entitlement shell — D1.7 + D2.1 hook contract.
   Per Q-WP1/Q-WP4/Q-WP5/Q-WP6 (D1.7, locked 2026-06-22).
   Static-shell defaults render gracefully even if Worker SSR fails. Per
   Q-WP6 (idempotent reload), nothing on this surface changes between
   first load and Nth reload. Worker mutates the data-hook nodes
   server-side via HTMLRewriter to fill in tier + access details. No
   client-side state, no time-decay copy. Per Q-WP3, Clay tokens render
   only when the resolved tier is the All-Access path; the static shell
   defaults to no-Clay (Newsletter palette). #}
<div data-hook="entitlement-shell" data-state="pending">
  <p data-hook="entitlement-acknowledgment" class="el-welcome__ack">You're in.</p>

  <p class="el-welcome__promise-sub">Intelligence and solutions elevating businesses to AI speeds.</p>

  <dl class="el-welcome__details">
    <dt>Tier</dt>
    <dd><span data-hook="entitlement-tier">Your subscription is active. We're loading your tier details now.</span></dd>

    <dt>Access</dt>
    <dd>
      <ul data-hook="entitlement-swimlanes">
        <li>Loading&hellip;</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt>Next billing</dt>
    <dd><time data-hook="entitlement-billing-next" datetime="">&mdash;</time></dd>

    <dt>Manage subscription</dt>
    <dd><a data-hook="entitlement-portal-link" href="">Open subscriber portal</a></dd>
  </dl>

  <aside data-hook="entitlement-failure" hidden>
    {# Failure copy populated by Worker per Q-WP5.a / b / c — the Worker
       selects which case and writes both headline + body via HTMLRewriter. #}
    <h2 data-hook="entitlement-failure-headline">We can't read that subscription link.</h2>
    <p data-hook="entitlement-failure-message">
      The link in your welcome email expires after a short window for security reasons. If you clicked an older copy of the email, or the link came from somewhere else, that's the cause.
    </p>
  </aside>
</div>
